  <h2 style="font-size:1.1rem; margin-top:3rem;">Cooperativeness Scoring</h2>

  <p>The system scores how cooperative a renter is on a 0-100 scale. It starts at 50 (neutral) and moves based on behavior. Respond within 2 hours? +15. Send documents without being asked twice? +15. Go silent for 48 hours after a doc request? -15. Ask three times for the same information without delivering? -20. The score determines the recommended approach — direct ask, reluctant concede, back off, or let the cadence handle it.</p>

  <pre style="background:#0a0a0a; border:1px solid #222; padding:1.5rem; font-size:0.8rem; line-height:1.6; color:#888; overflow-x:auto; margin:2rem 0;">
# Cooperativeness scoring — from approval_engine.py

def score_cooperativeness(chat_messages, deal_stage):
    score = 50.0  # starts neutral

    Response < 2 hours:          +15
    Proactive ("when/ready/send"): +10 to +20
    Docs sent unprompted:        +15
    Response > 48 hours:         -15
    Pushback ("why/scam/uncomfortable"): -10 to -25
    Asked 3x, sent 0 docs:      -20
    Silent after doc request:    -15
    "Looking elsewhere":         -10

    Returns:
      score:    0-100
      level:    COOPERATIVE | HESITANT | RESISTANT | EVASIVE
      approach: direct_ask | reluctant_concede | back_off | let_cadence_handle</pre>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.1rem; margin-top:3rem;">The Document Pipeline</h2>

  <p>Renters email documents to renterdocs@homeeasy.com. Gmail API polls every 5 minutes. AI classifies each document — pay stub, bank statement, ID, voucher letter. The approval engine scores against building criteria: income at least 2.5x monthly rent (Section 8 exempt), background check passes (non-violent, over 3 years is OK), all required docs present. Asana tickets get created for the building manager with the full assessment.</p>

  <pre style="background:#0a0a0a; border:1px solid #222; padding:1.5rem; font-size:0.8rem; line-height:1.6; color:#888; overflow-x:auto; margin:2rem 0;">
